GB-Scale Data Processing with Apache Spark
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line skills
Understanding of Python programming fundamentals
Familiarity with data processing concepts (filtering, aggregation, joins)
Basic knowledge of distributed computing principles
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure Apache Spark on a single Linux machine
Load and process large datasets using Spark DataFrames
Apply transformations and actions on GB-scale data
Optimize Spark jobs for performance
Save processed results in various formats
Environment Setup
Install Java Development Kit
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y openjdk-11-jdk
java -version
Install Apache Spark
cd ~
wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/spark/spark-3.4.1/spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3.tgz
tar -xzf spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3.tgz
sudo mv spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3 /opt/spark
Configure Environment Variables
echo 'export SPARK_HOME=/opt/spark' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:$SPARK_HOME/bin:$SPARK_HOME/sbin' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PYSPARK_PYTHON=python3' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
Verify Installation
spark-submit --version
pyspark --version
Install Python Dependencies
sudo apt install -y python3-pip
pip3 install pyspark pandas
