Conclusion
You have successfully processed GB-scale data using Apache Spark on a single machine. You learned to:

Configure Spark for local processing with appropriate memory settings
Load and clean large CSV datasets efficiently
Perform complex aggregations and transformations on millions of records
Optimize Spark jobs using caching and partitioning
Export results in multiple formats (CSV, Parquet, JSON)
These skills form the foundation for working with distributed data processing systems. Spark's ability to handle large datasets on a single machine demonstrates its efficiency, while the same code can scale to multi-node clusters for even larger workloads.

Next Steps: Explore Spark SQL for more complex queries, experiment with different file formats (Avro, ORC), or investigate Spark's machine learning library (MLlib) for predictive analytics on large datasets.
